description: Alpinia galanga, commonly known as Greater Galangal, is a rhizomatous plant native to Southeast Asia. It is widely used in traditional medicine and as a spice in cooking. The plant is aromatic, with its rhizomes having a pungent flavor, often compared to ginger. It has anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and digestive properties.
advantages: Used to reduce inflammation, making it helpful for conditions like arthritis.
disadvantages: Some individuals may experience allergic reactions such as skin irritation or respiratory discomfort.

description: Commonly known as Green Amaranth, this herbaceous plant is a fast-growing leafy vegetable and weed found in tropical and subtropical regions. It is rich in iron, calcium, and vitamins. The leaves are used in traditional cooking and for treating digestive issues, fever, and inflammation.
advantages: Known for being a good plant-based protein source, especially beneficial for vegetarians and vegans.
disadvantages: May accumulate nitrates from the soil, especially if grown in contaminated areas, which can convert into harmful nitrites in the body

description: Jackfruit is the largest tree-borne fruit, native to South Asia. The tree is evergreen and produces sweet, fibrous, and starchy fruits consumed fresh or cooked. Jackfruit seeds are also edible and nutritious. The tree is valued for its timber, and its leaves are used as fodder.
advantages: Despite its sweetness, jackfruit is relatively low in calories, making it suitable for healthy diets.
disadvantages: Some individuals may be allergic to jackfruit, experiencing symptoms such as itching, swelling, or breathing difficulties

description: Neem is a fast-growing, evergreen tree native to the Indian subcontinent. It is highly regarded in Ayurveda for its antifungal, antibacterial, and anti-inflammatory properties. Neem leaves, bark, seeds, and oil are used for medicinal, agricultural, and cosmetic purposes.
advantages: Neem supports the immune system, helping the body fight off infections and diseases.
disadvantages: Overconsumption of neem leaves or products may cause stomach upset, nausea, or diarrhea.

description: Known as Malabar Spinach, this vine is a fast-growing perennial found in tropical Asia and Africa. Its leaves are rich in vitamins A and C and are used in soups and curries. The plant has cooling and laxative properties.
advantages: Improves digestion, prevents constipation, and supports gut health.
disadvantages: Excessive consumption may lead to bloating, gas, or mild stomach upset due to its high fiber content.

description: Indian Mustard is cultivated for its seeds, which are used to produce mustard oil and condiments. The leaves are consumed as a green vegetable. It has anti-inflammatory properties and is used in traditional medicine for rheumatism and colds.
advantages: Mustard seeds can boost metabolism, aiding in fat burning and weight management
disadvantages: Mustard oil should be used cautiously during pregnancy. It has been associated with potential toxicity and may cause harm to the fetus in large quantities.

description: Karanda is a shrub that bears small, tangy fruits used in pickles and jams. It is a drought-resistant plant with high medicinal value, including antidiabetic and antioxidant properties.
advantages: Rich in vitamin C, iron, and antioxidants, it helps boost immunity and prevent diseases.
disadvantages: The plant has sharp thorns, which can make harvesting and handling difficult.

description: Lemon is a small evergreen tree cultivated for its sour fruits. Lemons are rich in vitamin C and are widely used in culinary applications, cleaning products, and traditional medicine to treat scurvy and colds.
advantages: High in vitamin C, supporting immunity and skin health.
disadvantages: Excessive consumption can lead to acid reflux or worsen conditions like GERD (gastroesophageal reflux disease).

description: This deciduous tree is known for its large leaves and edible fruits. The fruits are consumed fresh or dried and are used to treat gastrointestinal disorders. The tree is also valued for soil conservation.
advantages: The fruit is rich in dietary fiber, vitamins, and minerals, supporting digestive health and overall nutrition.
disadvantages: In some areas, the tree might grow aggressively, competing with other vegetation and potentially becoming invasive.

description: Revered in many cultures, the Peepal Tree is a large, long-living tree with heart-shaped leaves. It plays a role in traditional medicine for treating asthma, diabetes, and skin diseases.
advantages: The Peepal tree releases oxygen 24/7, making it highly beneficial for air quality.
disadvantages: Its roots can grow into building foundations, walls, and pipelines, causing structural damage.

description: Known as Chinese Hibiscus, this ornamental plant bears large, colorful flowers. It is used in traditional medicine for hair care, treating fevers, and as an anti-inflammatory agent.
advantages: The plant produces vibrant, large flowers that add aesthetic appeal to gardens and landscapes.
disadvantages: The blooms are short-lived, typically lasting only a day or two.

description: Jasmine plants are valued for their fragrant flowers, used in perfumery and essential oils. They are also used in teas and traditional medicine for relaxation and treating skin issues.
advantages: Used in traditional medicine to treat headaches, depression, and anxiety.
disadvantages: Requires regular pruning to manage growth and encourage flowering

description: Mango is a tropical fruit tree cultivated for its sweet, juicy fruits. Rich in vitamins A and C, mangoes are consumed fresh or processed. The leaves and bark are used in traditional medicine for treating diabetes and diarrhea.
advantages: High antioxidant content helps combat free radicals and boost immunity.
disadvantages: Sensitive to frost, prolonged drought, and waterlogging

description: Mint is a herbaceous perennial plant with aromatic leaves. It is used in culinary dishes, teas, and traditional medicine for its cooling and digestive properties.
advantages: Contains vitamins (A and C), minerals (iron, calcium), and antioxidants that support overall health.
disadvantages: Fungal diseases such as rust or mildew can occur in overly humid conditions

description: Often referred to as the "Miracle Tree," Moringa is rich in nutrients and antioxidants. Its leaves, pods, seeds, and roots are used in food and medicine for treating malnutrition, inflammation, and infections.
advantages: High in vitamins (A, C, E), minerals (calcium, potassium, and iron), and protein.
disadvantages: Can become invasive in certain regions, competing with native plants

description: This fast-growing tree produces small, sweet, cherry-like fruits. The fruits are rich in antioxidants, and the plant is used in traditional medicine for treating ulcers and pain.
advantages: The small, sweet fruits are edible and can be consumed fresh or used in jams, desserts, and drinks.
disadvantages: The wood is soft and not durable for long-term construction or heavy-duty uses.

description: Curry leaves are aromatic and widely used in Indian cuisine. They have antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and digestive properties and are used in traditional medicine for diabetes and hair care.
advantages: Rich in essential nutrients like calcium, iron, magnesium, phosphorus, and vitamins A, B, C, and E
disadvantages: Vulnerable to pests like aphids, scale insects, and caterpillars.

description: Oleander is a toxic yet ornamental shrub with fragrant flowers. Despite its toxicity, it is used in small doses in traditional medicine for treating heart conditions and skin disorders.
advantages: Highly drought-tolerant and thrives in poor soils, making it suitable for dry or arid regions.
disadvantages: Handling the plant without gloves may cause skin irritation in sensitive individuals.

description: Parijata is a sacred plant with fragrant flowers that bloom at night. It is used in traditional medicine to treat fever, arthritis, and respiratory ailments.
advantages: The leaves are used to treat joint pain, malaria, and fever.
disadvantages: Regular cleaning is required as the fallen flowers can litter the ground.

description: Known as Holy Basil, Tulsi is an aromatic plant revered in Ayurveda. It has adaptogenic, antimicrobial, and anti-inflammatory properties and is used for boosting immunity and treating respiratory conditions.
advantages: Tulsi is rich in antioxidants and compounds that support immune function, helping to fight off infections.
disadvantages: Tulsi requires regular pruning to maintain a bushy, healthy appearance and prevent it from becoming leggy or overgrown.

description: The Betel plant is a climbing vine whose leaves are used in traditional medicine and rituals. Betel leaves have digestive, antimicrobial, and stimulant properties.
advantages: The leaves have antimicrobial and antibacterial properties that help fight infections.
disadvantages: The plant can be susceptible to pests like aphids, whiteflies, and fungal diseases.

description: Mexican Mint, also known as Indian Borage, is an aromatic herb used for treating coughs, colds, and digestive disorders. Its leaves are often used in teas and home remedies for respiratory and skin conditions.
advantages: The flowers of Mexican Mint attract pollinators such as bees and butterflies, which contribute to garden biodiversity.
disadvantages: Due to its distinct taste, it may not complement all dishes, limiting its culinary versatility in some contexts.

description: Indian Beech is a fast-growing tree with medicinal, agricultural, and biofuel applications. Its seeds are used to produce biodiesel, while the leaves and bark have anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties.
advantages: The oil extracted from the seeds is sometimes used as a remedy for constipation and digestive issues.
disadvantages: It thrives best in hot, humid environments, and its growth may be stunted in cooler climates or areas with harsh winters.

description: Guava is a tropical fruit rich in vitamin C and dietary fiber. The leaves are used in traditional medicine for treating diarrhea, diabetes, and infections. The fruit is consumed fresh or processed into jams, juices, and desserts.
advantages: Guava is rich in dietary fiber, which supports healthy digestion, prevents constipation, and may help lower cholesterol levels.
disadvantages: Guava is also prone to bacterial infections like bacterial blight, which can harm the tree and reduce fruit production.

description: Pomegranate is a fruit-bearing shrub or tree valued for its antioxidant-rich seeds. The juice and seeds are used to support heart health and improve skin health. The peel and bark are used in traditional medicine for digestive issues.
advantages: The high fiber content promotes healthy digestion and prevents constipation.
disadvantages: Some people may experience allergic reactions, such as itching, swelling, or difficulty breathing, after consuming pomegranate.

description: Sandalwood is a highly valued tree known for its fragrant heartwood. The oil is used in perfumery, cosmetics, and aromatherapy. It also has antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties and is used in traditional medicine for skin disorders and stress relief.
advantages: Sandalwood oil is rich in antioxidants, which help reduce wrinkles, fine lines, and other signs of aging.
disadvantages: The high value of sandalwood has led to illegal harvesting, which threatens its population and biodiversity in its native habitats.

description: Jamun is a tropical tree producing small, purple fruits with a sweet-tart flavor. The fruit and seeds are used to manage diabetes, improve digestion, and boost immunity. The tree also has environmental significance for soil conservation.
advantages: Jamun’s vitamins and minerals support healthy hair growth and prevent hair fall.
disadvantages: Some individuals may experience allergic reactions to jamun, particularly in the form of itching, rashes, or swelling.

description: Rose Apple is a tropical fruit tree producing fragrant, bell-shaped fruits. The fruits are consumed fresh or used in desserts. The plant is used in traditional medicine for treating liver problems and infections.
advantages: They are low in calories, making them a great snack for those looking to maintain a healthy weight.
disadvantages: Rose apples have a short shelf life and are prone to spoilage if not consumed fresh, making them less convenient for long-term storage or transport.

description: Crape Jasmine is an ornamental shrub with white, star-shaped flowers. It is used in traditional medicine for its sedative and anti-inflammatory properties. The plant also has cultural significance in South Asia.
advantages: The plant is evergreen, providing lush, green foliage year-round, adding beauty to outdoor spaces even in the winter.
disadvantages: The plant can grow vigorously, requiring regular pruning to keep it from becoming unruly or taking over garden spaces.

description: Fenugreek is an annual herb with leaves and seeds used as a spice and in traditional medicine. It is known to aid in digestion, control blood sugar levels, and improve lactation. The seeds are also rich in dietary fiber and protein.
advantages: Fenugreek is commonly used as a galactagogue, a substance that promotes milk production in breastfeeding mothers.
disadvantages: Direct contact with fenugreek seeds or leaves may cause skin irritation or rashes in some people.
